text: Ann Reinking (November 10, 1949 â€“ December 12, 2020) was an American actress, dancer, and choreographer. Reinking was born in Seattle, Washington. Reinking acted in Coco (1969), Over Here! (1974), Goodtime Charley (1975), Chicago (1977), Dancin' (1978) and Sweet Charity (1986). She won a Tony Award for Best Choreography in 1996. For the 2000 West End production of Fosse, she won the Olivier Award for Best Theatre Choreographer. She was in the movies All That Jazz (1979), Annie (1982), and Micki & Maude (1984). Reinking died on December 12, 2020 in Seattle at the age of 71. ==References== Category:1949 births Category:2020 deaths Category:American movie actors Category:American stage actors Category:American television actors Category:American dancers Category:American choreographers Category:Tony Award winners Category:Actors from Seattle
